# LookingGlass Cyber ScoutVision Data Feed Splunk Technology Add-on

This software is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS, WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.

## Welcome to LookingGlass Cyber ScoutVision Data Feed Splunk Technology Add-on

#### The LookingGlass Cyber ScoutVision Data Feed Splunk Technology Add-on has been designed to collect data on a per-project basis from ScoutVision for use with Splunk.

#### Installation for a single server Splunk instance
Installing with Splunk Web for a single server Splunk instance
1) From the Splunk Web home screen, click the gear icon next to Apps.
2) Click Install app from file.
3) Locate Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_sv.tar.gz and click Upload
4) If Splunk Enterprise prompts you, click Yes to restart

Installing via CLI for a single server Splunk instance
1) Upload the Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_sv.tar.gz file to the Splunk instance
2) Extract the .tar.gz file in the apps directory of Splunk.  For example if your Splunk apps directory is located at /opt/splunk/etc/apps perform the following:
    a) sudo tar zxvf Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_sv.tar.gz -C /opt/splunk/etc/apps
3) Restart Splunk using /opt/splunk/bin/splunk restart

#### Installation for a distributed server Splunk environment
NOTE: The LookingGlass Cyber ScoutVision Data Feed Splunk Technology Add-on needs to be installed on a heavy forwarder in a distributed environment

Installing with Splunk Web for a distributed server Splunk environment
1) From the Splunk Web home screen on a heavy forwarder, click the gear icon next to Apps.
2) Click Install app from file.
3) Locate Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_sv.tar.gz and click Upload
4) If Splunk Enterprise prompts you, click Yes to restart

Installing via CLI for a distributed server Splunk environment
1) Upload the Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_sv.tar.gz file to a heavy forwarder
2) Extract the .tar.gz file in the apps directory of Splunk.  For example if your Splunk apps directory is located at /opt/splunk/etc/apps perform the following:
    a) sudo tar zxvf Splunk_TA_lookingglasscyber_sv.tar.gz -C /opt/splunk/etc/apps
3) Restart Splunk using /opt/splunk/bin/splunk restart

#### Configuration
Once the Splunk app has been installed, perform the following to configure the Technology Add-on:
1) From the Splunk Web home screen, click the gear icon next to Apps
2) From the list of Splunk apps and add-ons click on Set up under Actions for the LookingGlass Cyber ScoutVision Data Feed app
3) Ensure that Enable ScoutVision Integration is checked
4) Enter in the ScoutVision Project(s) that you would like to monitor using a comma to separate multiple projects in the ScoutVision Project(s) textbox
5) Enter in the domain name of the ScoutVision instance you are using in the Scoutvision Domain text area
6) Ensure that the SV API Username is sv_api
7) Enter in the API key of the ScoutVision user that you will be using to pull data from in the text box.
    a) If you need to get the ScoutVision API key for the user, perform the following:
      i) Login to the ScoutVision instance as the user whose API key you will be using that has access to the projects that you want to collect data for
      ii) In the Right-hand corner of the ScoutVision UI, click in Hi <user> -> Account Settings
      iii) The API key that you will need to enter should be listed in the API Access Token section.
           If the user account does not have an API Token contact support@lookingglasscyber.com to have an API token created for the user.
8) (Optional) If the Splunk instance needs to use a proxy server to access the Internet ensure that Use a proxy server is checked
9) (Optional) Enter in the domain name and port information for the proxy server if the Splunk instance needs to use a proxy server to access the Internet
10) Click on Save in the lower right hand corner of the configuration screen when you are finished

NOTE: Since the API key is encrypted it will not be displayed in the UI after you save it and re-enter the setup screen

